# Language Policy

- All user-facing communication MUST be in Turkish.
- Explanations, instructions, and messages addressed to the user MUST be written in Turkish.

- All source code MUST be written in English.
- Variable names, method names, class names, file names, and identifiers MUST be English.
- ALL code comments MUST be written in English.

- Do NOT mix Turkish and English in the same context.
- Do NOT translate code identifiers into Turkish.
- Turkish language is allowed ONLY in user-facing text, never inside code.

- Prefer clear, professional Turkish when communicating with the user.
- Prefer simple, descriptive English in code and comments.